---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="OpenIT — Privacy">
  <h1>Privacy</h1>
  <p class="lede">Draft — superseded by Pinkfish's main privacy policy when published.</p>

  <h2>What stays on your machine</h2>
  <p>
    Everything in <code>~/OpenIT/&lt;orgId&gt;/</code> lives locally — projects,
    Claude conversation history, and the OpenIT plugin. Nothing in that
    directory leaves your Mac unless you choose to sync it (Pinkfish entities)
    or share it.
  </p>

  <h2>What goes to Pinkfish</h2>
  <p>
    When you connect OpenIT to a Pinkfish org, entities prefixed
    <code>openit-</code> mirror to the Pinkfish backend so they're available
    when you log in elsewhere. Specifically: datastores, filestores, knowledge
    bases, workflows, and agents tagged for OpenIT. Authentication uses an
    OAuth client-credentials runtime token; no Pinkfish password ever leaves
    your browser.
  </p>

  <h2>What goes to Anthropic</h2>
  <p>
    OpenIT uses Claude Code as its substrate. Prompts and the surrounding
    context that Claude Code chooses to include are sent to Anthropic per
    Anthropic's terms. OpenIT does not add additional telemetry on top of
    Claude's.
  </p>

  <h2>What goes to third parties</h2>
  <p>
    When Claude calls a connected SaaS (Slack, Zendesk, Salesforce, Jira, Okta,
    GitHub, Google, AWS, Azure…) through Pinkfish's gateway, the request is
    routed through your existing Pinkfish connections. Those calls are subject
    to Pinkfish's connection-level audit and the third party's own terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Crash + error telemetry</h2>
  <p>None in v0.1.0. If we add it, we'll update this page first.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions: <a href="mailto:hello@pinkfish.ai">hello@pinkfish.ai</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
